[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: Software component design
OPTIONS:
  MARKUP: Text

[GRAMMAR]
IMPORT_FROM_FILE: en_50716_grammar.sgra

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This document covers the Component Design phase for the software element of
the railway control and protection system identified below. It is prepared in
accordance with EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.4 (Component design), and collects
three output deliverables from Table A.1:

  15. Software Component Design Specification
  16. Software Component Test Specification
  17. Software Component Design Verification Report

BASIC and SIL_1 through SIL_4 fields are taken from EN 50716:2023:
- Table A.1 (docs 15, 16, 17): BASIC=--, SIL_1–4=HR.
- Table A.4 (design techniques): values vary per technique.
- Table A.20 (component techniques): values vary per technique.
- Table A.5 (analysis and test techniques): values vary per technique.

Instructions for use:
- UIDs follow convention: CD-xxx (requirements) and CT-xxx (test cases).
- Sections 2.1, 2.2, and 2.3 constitute one entry per software component.
  Duplicate all three sub-sections for each component listed in the
  architecture (SAD-011) and update the component identifier throughout.
- Duplicate CT-001 through CT-004 for each test case; assign a unique
  CT-xxx UID and set the RELATIONS VALUE to the SRS or CD requirement
  being verified.
- Delete this instruction block before formal release.
<<<

