[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Component interface specification

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: CD-020
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Component interface – fully defined – <COMP-ID>
STATEMENT: >>>
Component: <COMP-ID>

The component interface shall be fully defined in accordance with SAD-060
(fully defined interface principle) and EN 50716:2023, Table A.20. The
following tables constitute the complete interface contract; no interface
element may rely on implementation-defined or undocumented behaviour.

Function / entry point: <function_name>

  Parameter     | Direction | Type     | Range / valid values | Unit
  --------------|-----------|----------|---------------------|------
  <param_1>     | IN        | <type>   | [<min>..<max>]      | <unit>
  <param_2>     | IN        | <enum>   | {VAL_A, VAL_B, VAL_C}| –
  <param_3>     | OUT       | <type>   | [<min>..<max>]      | <unit>
  <return_code> | RETURN    | <enum>   | {OK, ERR_RANGE, ERR_HW} | –

Preconditions (caller shall ensure):
  - <param_1> is within [<min>..<max>] before the call.
  - <precondition 2>

Postconditions (component guarantees on return OK):
  - <param_3> is within [<min>..<max>].
  - Internal state variable <state_var_1> is updated.
  - <postcondition 3>

Error returns and their meaning:
  ERR_RANGE : <param_1> or <param_2> outside valid range; output unchanged.
  ERR_HW    : hardware read/write failed; safe state applied to output.

Side effects: <none / describe any persistent state changes>
Re-entrancy:  <Not re-entrant — single caller only / Re-entrant — protected by <mechanism>>
Maximum execution time: < <n> µs (WCET budget from SAD-052)
<<<
BASIC: R
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: M
SIL_4: M
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection, Review
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Table A.20 – Fully defined interface.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: CD-021
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Information hiding and encapsulation – <COMP-ID>
STATEMENT: >>>
Component: <COMP-ID>

The component shall apply information hiding: all internal state variables,
data structures, and implementation details shall be encapsulated and not
accessible to other components except through the defined interface (CD-020).

Specifically:
  a) All internal variables shall be declared with the minimum necessary
     scope (file-scope static where possible; no external linkage for
     internal data).
  b) Internal data structures shall not be exposed in public headers.
     Only opaque handles or defined interface types may appear in the
     public interface.
  c) No other component may modify the internal state of <COMP-ID> except
     by calling its published interface functions.
  d) Configuration constants and calibration values used only internally
     shall be defined within the component translation unit, not in
     shared headers.

The header file(s) published by <COMP-ID>: <header file name(s)>
Internal (private) source files: <source file name(s)>
<<<
