SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Table A.20 – Information hiding and encapsulation.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: CD-022
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Parameter number limit – <COMP-ID>
STATEMENT: >>>
Component: <COMP-ID>

The number of parameters for each function or procedure in the component
shall be limited to support readability, testability, and static analysis.

  Maximum number of parameters per function: <n> (recommended: ≤ 6)

Functions that appear to require more parameters shall be refactored by:
  a) Grouping logically related parameters into a well-defined structure,
     with the structure fully specified per CD-020.
  b) Splitting the function into smaller, more focused sub-functions.

Current parameter counts:
  <function_name_1> : <n> parameters
  <function_name_2> : <n> parameters

Any function exceeding the limit shall require documented justification
approved by the Software Verifier.
<<<
