[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Component internal design

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: CD-030
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Algorithm and processing logic – <COMP-ID>
STATEMENT: >>>
Component: <COMP-ID>

The processing logic of the component shall be described at sufficient
detail for an independent implementer to produce a conforming implementation
without reference to any other document.

Processing sequence:

  Step 1 – Input validation (SAD-030):
    Validate <param_1>: if outside [<min>..<max>], return ERR_RANGE.
    Validate <param_2>: if not in {VAL_A, VAL_B, VAL_C}, return ERR_RANGE.

  Step 2 – Core computation:
    <Describe the algorithm in plain language or structured pseudocode.
    Reference any applicable standard algorithm, formula, or look-up table.
    Identify any numerical precision or rounding requirements.>

    Example:
      result = f(<param_1>, <param_2>)
      where f is defined as: <formula or reference to Annex>

  Step 3 – Output assignment:
    Assign computed result to <param_3>.
    Apply saturation / clamping to [<min>..<max>] before assignment.

  Step 4 – Post-assertion (SAD-033):
    Assert: <param_3> is within [<min>..<max>].
    Assert: internal state is self-consistent.

Look-up tables or formulae: <figure reference / attached table / "N/A">
Numerical precision: <floating-point / fixed-point, precision required>
Known edge cases and their handling:
  <Edge case 1>: <handling>
  <Edge case 2>: <handling>
<<<
