[REQUIREMENT]
UID: CD-031
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: State machine specification – <COMP-ID>
STATEMENT: >>>
Component: <COMP-ID>

If the component implements state-dependent behaviour, the complete state
machine shall be specified below. If the component is stateless, state
"Stateless: this component holds no persistent state between calls."

States:
  State        | Entry action          | Exit action
  -------------|----------------------|------------------
  <STATE_INIT> | Initialise variables  | –
  <STATE_IDLE> | –                     | –
  <STATE_RUN>  | Start processing      | Record last output
  <STATE_FAIL> | Apply safe state      | Log fault

Transitions:
  From state    | Event / condition       | Guard               | To state
  --------------|-------------------------|---------------------|-------------
  <STATE_INIT>  | Initialisation complete | No faults detected  | <STATE_IDLE>
  <STATE_IDLE>  | Activation command      | Input valid         | <STATE_RUN>
  <STATE_RUN>   | Fault detected          | –                   | <STATE_FAIL>
  <STATE_FAIL>  | Reset command           | Fault cleared       | <STATE_INIT>

State diagram reference: <figure number or "see attached diagram">

All states and all transitions shall be reachable (no dead states or
unreachable transitions). This shall be verified by review (CD-060).
The safe state <STATE_FAIL> shall always be reachable from any state
upon detection of a fault condition.
<<<
