[REQUIREMENT]
UID: CD-032
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Data structures and type definitions – <COMP-ID>
STATEMENT: >>>
Component: <COMP-ID>

All data types, structures, and enumerations used by the component shall
be explicitly defined. No use of implicit types, magic numbers, or
platform-dependent type sizes is permitted.

Internal data types:

  Type name       | Base type     | Range / members                | Used for
  ----------------|---------------|--------------------------------|------------------
  <CompState_t>   | enum (uint8)  | STATE_INIT=0, IDLE=1, ...      | Component state
  <CompInput_t>   | struct        | {field1: int16, field2: uint8} | Input bundle
  <CompOutput_t>  | struct        | {result: int32, code: uint8}   | Output bundle
  <CompConfig_t>  | const struct  | {min: int16, max: int16, ...}  | Configuration

Memory allocation:
  All data structures used by <COMP-ID> shall be statically allocated.
  Dynamic memory allocation is prohibited (SAD-042 / SRS-051).

  Static RAM footprint: <n> bytes (matches SAD-052 budget)
  ROM footprint (code + const data): <n> bytes

Shared data items (if any):
  <data_item>: shared with <COMP-ID> via <mechanism>; consistency guaranteed
  by <mutex name / interrupt disable scope>.
<<<
