[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Design constraints

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The following requirements specify the design and implementation constraints
applicable at component level, taken from EN 50716:2023, Tables A.4 and A.20.
These requirements apply to every component in the Component Design Specification
and complement the architecture-level constraints in SAD-040 through SAD-044.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: CD-040
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Modular approach at component level
STATEMENT: >>>
Each software component shall embody the modular approach mandated by the
architecture (SAD-040). At the component level this means:

  a) Each source file implements exactly one component; no component spans
     multiple source files unless a defined split (e.g. public/private header)
     is explicitly specified in the component interface (CD-020).
  b) Component size limit: < <n> lines of source code (executable statements),
     consistent with the architecture limit in SAD-040.
  c) Each sub-function within the component shall have a single, identifiable
     purpose; sub-functions exceeding <n> lines shall be decomposed further.
  d) The set of functions exported by the component shall be the minimum
     necessary to satisfy the allocated SRS requirements; no internal helpers
     shall be exported.

Compliance shall be verified by static analysis (CD-052) and code inspection
(CD-060).
<<<
BASIC: HR
SIL_1: M
SIL_2: M
SIL_3: M
SIL_4: M
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection, Analysis
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Table A.4 – Modular approach.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: CD-041
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Component design principles (Table A.20)
STATEMENT: >>>
The design of each component shall conform to the component design principles
of EN 50716:2023, Table A.20, as implemented by CD-020 (fully defined
interface), CD-021 (information hiding), and CD-022 (parameter number limit).
The following additional principles apply:

  a) Each component shall be independently testable: it shall be possible to
     instantiate and exercise the component in isolation using a test harness,
     without linking to any component it does not directly use.
  b) The component shall have no hidden dependencies: all dependencies on
     other components, hardware drivers, or global state shall be explicitly
     declared in the interface (CD-020) or passed as parameters.
  c) The component shall not use global variables that are also modified by
     other components; any shared state shall be mediated via the defined
     interface or a dedicated shared-resource manager.
  d) Component configurations (calibration constants, timeout values, limits)
     shall be parameterisable through the interface or a defined configuration
     structure (CD-032), not hardcoded within the implementation.
<<<
