RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Table A.4 – Components (Table A.20).

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: CD-042
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Design and coding standards at component level
STATEMENT: >>>
The design and coding standards defined in SAD-041 apply in full to all
components. At the component level, the following additional requirements
apply:

  a) Every function shall have a header comment block stating: purpose,
     parameters (type, range, direction), return values, preconditions,
     postconditions, and SIL classification. The header shall be the
     authoritative source for the component's interface contract.
  b) Magic numbers are prohibited: all numerical constants shall be defined
     as named constants or enumeration members with a descriptive name and
     unit annotation (where applicable).
  c) All static analysis warnings generated by the project's static analysis
     tool configuration (CD-052) shall be resolved before the component
     design record is baselined. Each suppressed warning shall be documented
     with a justification record.
  d) The component source file shall include the applicable coding standard
     compliance header or comment block referencing the applicable version of
     the coding standard.

Coding standard: <reference to SAD-041 entry>
Static analysis tool: <reference to CD-052>
<<<
