[REQUIREMENT]
UID: CD-043
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Structured programming at component level
STATEMENT: >>>
All safety-related components shall be implemented using structured
programming as specified in SAD-042. The following component-level
metrics shall be tracked and reported in the verification report (CD-060):

  Cyclomatic complexity (McCabe): ≤ <n> per function (recommended ≤ 10).
  Control flow nesting depth:     ≤ <n> levels per function.
  Maximum function length:        ≤ <n> executable statements.

Functions exceeding any threshold shall be refactored or, if a justified
exception is granted, documented in the design deviation register with
the Verifier's approval.

Measurement tool: <static analysis tool from CD-052>
Results location: <report reference or tool output path>
<<<
