SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Analysis, Inspection
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Table A.4 – Structured programming.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: CD-044
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Analysable programs
STATEMENT: >>>
Each component shall be designed to be amenable to static analysis and
formal verification. The following design rules support analysability:

  a) Control flow shall be bounded: all loops shall have a statically
     determinable upper bound on the number of iterations; the bound shall
     be annotated in the source code and enforced by a static analysis rule.
  b) Recursion is prohibited in safety-critical components (consistent with
     SAD-042 and SRS-051).
  c) Pointer arithmetic shall be restricted to array indexing with
     bounds-checked indices; arbitrary pointer arithmetic is prohibited.
  d) Function pointers, if used, shall be restricted to a statically known
     set of targets; calls via function pointer shall be verified to point
     only to type-compatible functions within the permitted set.
  e) All data flow paths through each function shall be finitely enumerable
     for purposes of test coverage analysis (CD-053).

The static analysis tool configuration (CD-052) shall include rules that
enforce items (a) through (d) automatically.
<<<
BASIC: HR
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Analysis, Inspection
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Table A.4 – Analysable programs.

