TITLE: Software Component Test Specification

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This section constitutes the Software Component Test Specification as
required by EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.4 and Table A.1 (document 16). It
defines the strategy and sample test cases for verifying each software
component against its Component Design Specification (section 2).

Analysis and test techniques are selected per EN 50716:2023, Table A.5.
Duplicate the sample test case entries (CT-001 through CT-004) for each
actual test case and assign a unique CT-xxx UID.
<<<

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Component test strategy

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: CD-050
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Component test strategy overview
STATEMENT: >>>
Component testing (Level 1 in the overall test strategy, SRS-070) shall
verify each component against:
  a) Its interface specification (CD-020).
  b) Its processing logic and state machine (CD-030, CD-031).
  c) Its allocated SRS requirements (listed in CD-010).

Test scope: all software components with SIL ≥ 1 listed in the architecture
(SAD-011). Non-safety (SIL 0) components shall be tested to a level
commensurate with their interface to safety-critical components.

Test execution environment:
  Host / target:    <host PC with test framework / target hardware>
  Test framework:   <framework name and version — tool class T2, SP-082>
  Coverage tool:    <tool name and version — tool class T2, SP-082>

Entry criteria:
  - Component Design Specification (section 2) is baselined and verified
    (CD-060).
  - Test environment is set up and qualified.
  - Static analysis (CD-052) has been completed with no unresolved defects.

Exit criteria:
  - All test cases executed with PASS verdict.
  - Coverage objectives (CD-053) are met.
  - All Critical and Major findings resolved; residual findings assessed.
  - Test results reviewed and approved by the Software Verifier (SP-021).

Test traceability: each test case (CT-xxx) shall reference the SRS or
CD requirement it verifies via the RELATIONS / ROLE: Verifies field.
<<<
BASIC: --
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.4 and Table A.1, doc 16 – Component Test Specification.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: CD-051
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Dynamic analysis
STATEMENT: >>>
Dynamic analysis (black-box and white-box testing) shall be applied to
all safety-related components in accordance with EN 50716:2023, Table A.5
(Dynamic analysis, reference Table A.13).

Black-box test techniques applied:
  - Equivalence partitioning: partition each input domain into classes of
    equivalent behaviour; test at least one value per class.
  - Boundary value analysis: test at the boundary values and immediately
    adjacent values for each equivalence class.
  - Decision table testing (where applicable, per SRS-062): exercise each
    combination of conditions in the decision tables (CD-030).
  - State transition testing (where applicable, per CD-031): exercise all
    defined state transitions and verify that undefined transitions do not
    occur.

White-box test techniques applied:
  - Path testing: exercise all feasible control flow paths through each
    function; report unfeasible paths with justification.
  - Data flow testing: exercise definition-use pairs for safety-critical
    variables.

The combination of black-box and white-box techniques shall achieve the
coverage objectives in CD-053.
<<<
BASIC: HR
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: M
SIL_4: M
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Testing, Analysis
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Table A.5 – Dynamic analysis (Table A.13).

