Formal mathematical proof shall be applied to verify critical properties
of safety-related components where testing alone is insufficient to achieve
the required confidence at the target SIL. Formal proof shall be applied
in accordance with EN 50716:2023, Table A.5.

Scope of formal proof for this project:
  <Describe which components or properties are subject to formal proof.
  If not applied, state: "Formal proof is not applied at this SIL level;
  the combination of dynamic analysis (CD-051), static analysis (CD-052),
  and coverage (CD-053) is sufficient to achieve the required confidence."
  Ensure consistency with the hazard analysis and SVP (SP-072).>

Properties to be proved (if applicable):
  - <Property 1, e.g. "Output is always within [min..max] for any valid input">
  - <Property 2, e.g. "The component always terminates in finite time">

Proof method / tool: <e.g. Frama-C / SPARK / Coq / manual proof>
Proof artefacts location: <document ID or repository path>
<<<
