[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Static analysis requirements

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: CD-052
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Static analysis configuration and execution
STATEMENT: >>>
Static analysis shall be applied to the source code of all safety-related
components in accordance with EN 50716:2023, Table A.5 (Static analysis,
reference Table A.19) and the tool qualification requirements in SP-082.

Tool and configuration:
  Tool name:        <static analysis tool>
  Tool version:     <version>
  Rule set:         <e.g. MISRA C:2012 mandatory + required rules; project
                    rule set document ID>
  Additional rules: <project-specific rules, e.g. banned functions,
                    complexity limits per CD-043>

Execution requirements:
  a) Static analysis shall be executed on the complete translation unit for
     each component (not individual functions in isolation).
  b) All analysis warnings shall be reviewed; each warning shall be either:
       - Resolved by correcting the source code, or
       - Documented with a justified deviation approved by the Verifier.
  c) The analysis shall be re-executed after any change to the source code
     until the component baseline is established.
  d) The analysis report shall be included in the component baseline under
     configuration management (SP-060).

Checks performed (minimum):
  - Coding standard compliance (CD-042)
  - Cyclomatic complexity per function (CD-043)
  - Control flow bounds (CD-044)
  - Uninitialised variables, unreachable code, stack usage estimation
  - Banned function usage (e.g. gets, sprintf, malloc after init)

Analysis report reference: <document ID or tool output location>
<<<
