[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Test coverage objectives

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: CD-053
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Test coverage objectives
STATEMENT: >>>
Structural test coverage shall be measured for all safety-related components
and shall meet the following minimum objectives in accordance with
EN 50716:2023, Table A.5 (Test coverage, reference Table A.21), consistent
with the project-level objectives defined in SRS-073:

  SIL 1: Statement coverage (SC):        100 % of executable statements.
  SIL 2: Branch coverage (BC):           100 % of branches (decisions).
  SIL 3: Branch coverage (BC):           100 %;
          MC/DC:                          HR – apply to safety-critical components.
  SIL 4: Modified Condition / Decision
          Coverage (MC/DC):               100 % of safety-critical components.

Coverage measurement:
  Tool:         <coverage tool name and version — tool class T2, SP-082>
  Granularity:  per-function and per-component coverage reported separately.
  Exclusions:   defensive-programming error handlers that cannot be exercised
                without hardware fault injection shall be excluded and
                documented with justification; compensated by static analysis.

Coverage gaps (statements or branches not reachable by dynamic test) shall
be justified and compensated by static analysis (CD-052) or formal proof
(CD-056), with evidence recorded in the verification report (CD-061).

Coverage results location: <report reference or tool output path>
<<<
