[REQUIREMENT]
UID: CD-054
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Performance testing
STATEMENT: >>>
Performance testing shall be applied to all safety-related components to
confirm that timing budgets and resource limits defined in the component
design (SAD-052) are met, in accordance with EN 50716:2023, Table A.5
(Performance testing, reference Table A.18).

Measurements required per component:

  Metric                  | Limit           | Method
  ------------------------|-----------------|-----------------------------
  WCET                    | < <n> µs        | Measurement on target or
                          |                 | static WCET tool (see below)
  Stack depth (max)       | < <n> bytes     | Instrumented or static
  RAM usage (static)      | < <n> bytes     | Linker map file
  ROM / code size         | < <n> bytes     | Linker map file

WCET measurement method:
  <Instrumented measurement on target hardware under worst-case stimulus /
  Static WCET analysis tool — reference tool qualification SP-082>

Conditions for WCET measurement:
  Worst-case input values as identified by the algorithm analysis (CD-030).
  Worst-case concurrent task load per SAD-021.

Performance test results location: <report reference or tool output path>
<<<
BASIC: --
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Testing, Analysis
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Table A.5 – Performance testing (Table A.18).

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: CD-055
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Interface testing
STATEMENT: >>>
Interface testing shall be applied to verify the correct behaviour of each
component at its interface boundary, in accordance with EN 50716:2023,
Table A.5 (Interface testing).

Interface test requirements:

  a) All input parameters shall be tested at:
       - Nominal values (representative of normal operation).
       - Boundary values (minimum, maximum, and values immediately outside
         the valid range — per CD-020 and CD-022).
       - Invalid / out-of-range values (verify ERR_RANGE is returned and
         the output is not corrupted).
       - Combinations of parameters that trigger distinct processing paths
         (equivalence classes, per CD-051).

  b) All error return codes defined in the interface specification (CD-020)
     shall be exercised by at least one test case.

  c) Pre-condition violations shall be injected (within the test harness)
     to verify that the component's defensive checks detect them (SAD-030).

  d) For components with state (CD-031): the interface shall be tested in
     each relevant state, and invalid calls in wrong states shall be verified
     to be rejected.

Interface test cases are included in the sample test cases (CT-xxx) below.
Interface test coverage shall be included in the coverage report (CD-053).
<<<
BASIC: HR
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Testing, Inspection
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Table A.5 – Interface testing.

