[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Sample test cases

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The following test cases are template entries. Duplicate for each actual
test case, assign a unique CT-xxx UID, and set the RELATIONS VALUE to the
SRS or CD requirement being verified. Set VERDICT to NOT_RUN before
execution; update ACTUAL_RESULT and VERDICT after execution.
<<<

[TEST_CASE]
UID: CT-001
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: <COMP-ID> – nominal operation – <brief description>
TEST_TYPE: Unit
PRECONDITIONS: >>>
- <COMP-ID> is initialised (state = STATE_IDLE or equivalent).
- Input <param_1> is set to a nominal value within [<min>..<max>].
- Input <param_2> is set to VAL_A (valid enumeration member).
- No fault flags are active; no previous error state.
<<<
STEPS: >>>
1. Set <param_1> = <nominal value>.
2. Set <param_2> = VAL_A.
3. Call <function_name>(<param_1>, <param_2>, &<param_3>).
4. Record return code and <param_3>.
5. Record component state and any fault log entries.
<<<
EXPECTED_RESULT: >>>
- Return code: OK.
- <param_3> = <expected computed value> ± <tolerance>.
- Component state: <STATE_RUN> (or unchanged if stateless).
- No fault log entries generated.
- Execution time: < <n> µs (performance budget from SAD-052).
<<<
ACTUAL_RESULT: >>>
<To be completed upon test execution>
<<<
VERDICT: NOT_RUN
DATE_EXECUTED: <YYYY-MM-DD>
TESTER: <Name>
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SRS-020
  ROLE: Verifies

[TEST_CASE]
UID: CT-002
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: <COMP-ID> – boundary values – <brief description>
TEST_TYPE: Unit
PRECONDITIONS: >>>
- <COMP-ID> is initialised (state = STATE_IDLE or equivalent).
- No fault flags are active.
<<<
STEPS: >>>
For each boundary value combination:
  a) <param_1> = <min>: call <function_name> and record result.
  b) <param_1> = <max>: call <function_name> and record result.
  c) <param_1> = <min - 1> (below range): call and record result.
  d) <param_1> = <max + 1> (above range): call and record result.
Record return code, <param_3>, state, and fault log for each case.
<<<
EXPECTED_RESULT: >>>
a) <param_1> = <min>: OK; <param_3> = <expected minimum output>.
b) <param_1> = <max>: OK; <param_3> = <expected maximum output>.
c) <param_1> = <min - 1>: ERR_RANGE; <param_3> unchanged; fault logged.
d) <param_1> = <max + 1>: ERR_RANGE; <param_3> unchanged; fault logged.
No uncontrolled exception, watchdog timeout, or memory corruption in any case.
<<<
ACTUAL_RESULT: >>>
<To be completed upon test execution>
<<<
VERDICT: NOT_RUN
DATE_EXECUTED: <YYYY-MM-DD>
TESTER: <Name>
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SRS-020
  ROLE: Verifies

[TEST_CASE]
UID: CT-003
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: <COMP-ID> – fault injection – safe state on hardware error
TEST_TYPE: Unit
PRECONDITIONS: >>>
- <COMP-ID> is initialised and in STATE_RUN.
- A fault injection mechanism is available to simulate a hardware read
  failure (e.g. stub returning ERR_HW from the HW abstraction layer).
<<<
STEPS: >>>
1. Configure fault injection: next call to <hw_read_function> returns ERR_HW.
2. Call <function_name> with valid inputs.
3. Record return code, <param_3>, component state, and fault log.
4. Remove fault injection; call <function_name> again with valid inputs.
5. Record return code and state after fault removal.
<<<
EXPECTED_RESULT: >>>
Step 3:
  - Return code: ERR_HW.
  - <param_3> is set to the defined safe default value.
  - Component state transitions to STATE_FAIL.
  - Fault log entry created with correct fault code and timestamp.

Step 5:
  - Component remains in STATE_FAIL (fault must be explicitly cleared).
  - Return code: ERR_HW or a "fault active" code.
  - No further processing of outputs until fault is cleared via reset.
<<<
ACTUAL_RESULT: >>>
<To be completed upon test execution>
<<<
VERDICT: NOT_RUN
DATE_EXECUTED: <YYYY-MM-DD>
TESTER: <Name>
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SRS-020
  ROLE: Verifies

[TEST_CASE]
UID: CT-004
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: <COMP-ID> – interface test – precondition violation detection
TEST_TYPE: Unit
PRECONDITIONS: >>>
- <COMP-ID> is initialised.
- Test harness can supply NULL pointers or invalid parameter combinations.
<<<
STEPS: >>>
1. Call <function_name> with <param_3> = NULL (null output pointer).
2. Record return code, component state, and fault log.
3. Call <function_name> with <param_1> valid but <param_2> = invalid enum
   value (a value not in {VAL_A, VAL_B, VAL_C}).
4. Record return code, <param_3>, and fault log.
5. Call <function_name> with all parameters valid after the above failures.
6. Record return code and <param_3>.
<<<
EXPECTED_RESULT: >>>
Step 2: Return code ERR_RANGE or equivalent; no write through NULL pointer;
        no memory corruption; fault logged.
Step 4: Return code ERR_RANGE; <param_3> not written; fault logged.
Step 6: Return code OK; component returns to normal operation;
        <param_3> = <expected value>.
<<<
ACTUAL_RESULT: >>>
<To be completed upon test execution>
<<<
VERDICT: NOT_RUN
DATE_EXECUTED: <YYYY-MM-DD>
TESTER: <Name>
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SRS-031
  ROLE: Verifies

