[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Software Component Design Verification Report

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This section constitutes the Software Component Design Verification Report
as required by EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.4 and Table A.1 (document 17). It
records the outcome of independent verification of the Component Design
Specification (section 2) and the Component Test Specification (section 3)
before those documents are baselined and implementation commences.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: CD-060
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Verification scope and method
STATEMENT: >>>
The component design verification shall cover all deliverables in this document:

  a) Component Design Specification (section 2), for each component:
       - Completeness: the component design covers all SRS requirements
         allocated to it (CD-010).
       - Interface correctness: the interface specification (CD-020) is
         fully defined per SAD-060 and Table A.20.
       - Logic correctness: the algorithm (CD-030), state machine (CD-031),
         and data structures (CD-032) are internally consistent and
         consistent with the SRS requirements.
       - Correct application of Table A.4 and A.20 constraints (CD-040
         through CD-044): complexity metrics within limits, encapsulation
         verified, parameter counts within limits.

  b) Component Test Specification (section 3):
       - Coverage: every requirement in section 2 has at least one test case
         (CT-xxx) with ROLE: Verifies traceability.
       - Adequacy: the test strategy (CD-050) and techniques (CD-051 through
         CD-056) are appropriate to the target SIL.
       - Static analysis configuration (CD-052) is complete and correct.
       - Coverage objectives (CD-053) are achievable and consistent with
         the project-level objectives (SRS-073).

Verification method: structured inspection by the Software Verifier (SP-021)
using a checklist derived from EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.4 and Table A.20.
Verifier: <Name, Organisation, independence evidence — see SP-021>
Checklist reference: <document ID or tool reference>
<<<
BASIC: --
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection, Review
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.4 and Table A.1, doc 17 – Component Design Verification Report.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: CD-061
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Verification records and verdict
STATEMENT: >>>
The Software Component Design Verification Report shall include:

  - Date and revision of the Component Design Specification and Component
    Test Specification reviewed (one entry per document).
  - Name, role, and independence evidence of the verifier (per SP-021).
  - Checklist results: each checklist item marked Pass / Fail / N/A
    with observations recorded.
  - List of findings: unique identifier, description, severity
    (Critical / Major / Minor / Observation), and status.
  - Metrics summary:
      - Cyclomatic complexity: maximum and average per component.
      - Code size: actual vs budget (SAD-052) per component.
      - Parameter counts: all within limit (CD-022).
  - Action items raised, with reference to the action item register.
  - Resolution evidence for all Critical and Major findings.
  - Overall verdict: Approved / Approved with conditions / Not approved.

The Component Design Specification shall not be baselined and
implementation shall not commence until an Approved verdict is recorded.

Verification Report reference: <document ID>
Verdict: <to be completed upon review>
Date of approval: <YYYY-MM-DD>
<<<
